@Node Main "gdbm.guide"
@Next "Copying"

   GNU @{b}dbm@{ub} is a library of functions implementing a hashed database on
a disk file.  This manual documents GNU @{b}dbm@{ub} Version 1.7.1 (@{b}gdbm@{ub}).  The
software was written by Philip A. Nelson. This document was originally
written by Pierre Gaumond from texts written by Phil.


Introduction:

 @{" Copying                   " Link "Copying"}  Your rights.
 @{" Intro                     " Link "Intro"}  Introduction to GNU dbm.
 @{" List                      " Link "List"}  List of functions.

Functions:

 @{" Open                      " Link "Open"}  Opening the database.
 @{" Close                     " Link "Close"}  Closing the database.
 @{" Store                     " Link "Store"}  Inserting and replacing records in the database.
 @{" Fetch                     " Link "Fetch"}  Searching records in the database.
 @{" Delete                    " Link "Delete"}  Removing records from the database.
 @{" Sequential                " Link "Sequential"}  Sequential access to records.
 @{" Reorganization            " Link "Reorganization"}  Database reorganization.
 @{" Sync                      " Link "Sync"}  Insure all writes to disk have competed.
 @{" Errors                    " Link "Errors"}  Convert internal error codes into English.
 @{" Options                   " Link "Options"}  Setting internal options.

Other topics:

 @{" Variables                 " Link "Variables"}  Two useful variables.
 @{" Compatibility             " Link "Compatibility"}  Compatibility with UNIX dbm and ndbm.
 @{" Conversion                " Link "Conversion"}  Converting dbm files to gdbm format.
 @{" Bugs                      " Link "Bugs"}  Problems and bugs.


@EndNode

